# Icon-only Refresh and Edit actions

Never render **Refresh** or **Edit** as visible button/link label text in the UI.

## Use shared components

- **Refresh** → `RefreshIconButton` (`src/components/ui/RefreshIconButton.svelte`)
- **Edit** → `EditIconButton` (`src/components/ui/EditIconButton.svelte`)

Both are icon-only controls. Pass meaning via `ariaLabel` (required) and optional `title` for hover tooltips.

```svelte
<!-- ✅ GOOD -->
<RefreshIconButton
  spinning={loading}
  ariaLabel={loading ? 'Refreshing join requests' : 'Refresh join requests'}
  on:click={refresh}
/>

<EditIconButton ariaLabel="Edit default EVM account" on:click={openEdit} />
```

```svelte
<!-- ❌ BAD -->
<button type="button" on:click={refresh}>Refresh</button>
<button type="button" on:click={openEdit}>Edit</button>
```

## Allowed exceptions

- **Status copy** is fine: “Refreshing…”, “Refreshing proposals…” (not action buttons).
- **Modal/page headings** may say “Edit …” when naming a form (`<h2>Edit profile</h2>`).
- **`aria-label` / `title`** should describe the action in plain language; they are not visible labels.

## New work

When adding reload or edit affordances in Svelte UI, default to the shared icon buttons. Do not introduce new text-labeled Refresh/Edit controls or duplicate inline refresh/pencil SVGs unless there is a strong layout reason — then still keep the control icon-only with accessible naming.
